citation.case_name: United States v. Marshall & Ilsley Bank Stock Corp.

html:
387 U.S. 238

87 S.Ct. 1706

18 L.Ed.2d 743

UNITED STATES
v.
MARSHALL & ILSLEY BANK STOCK CORP. et al.

No. 1017.

Supreme Court of the United States

May 22, 1967

Solicitor General Marshall, Assistant Attorney General Turner, Nathan Lewin, Howard E. Shapiro and Herbert G. Schoepke, for the United States.

Maxwell H. Herriott and Louis Quarles, for appellees.

PER CURIAM.

1

The judgment is reversed. Section 11(e) of the Bank Holding Company Act of 1956, as amended, 80 Stat. 241; United States v. First City National Bank of Houston, 386 U.S. 361, 87 S.Ct. 1088, 18 L.Ed.2d 151.
